RUSSIA DAYBOOK: Khodorkovsky, Qaddafi, BP-Rosneft, Severstal

-- B y   I l y a   A r k h i p o v
-- 
2011-05-17T04:53:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-17/russia-daybook-khodorkovsky-qaddafi-bp-rosneft-severstal.html
Former Yukos Oil Co. billionaire
Mikhail Khodorkovsky appeals his second fraud conviction in
Moscow City Court. Representatives of Libyan leader Muammar Qaddafi fly to Moscow for talks. OAO Severstal reports earnings.
 BP Plc (BP/)  and OAO Rosneft may comment on their proposed share swap
and Arctic cooperation accord.  ALL TIMES +4 GMT  WHAT TO WATCH:
*Khodorkovsky appeals December sentence that could keep him in
prison until 2017.
*Qaddafi may send envoys to Moscow for talks today amid an armed
rebellion at home and a decision by the International Criminal
Court to seek the leader’s arrest for alleged war crimes.
*Prime Minister Vladimir Putin holds government meeting in
Moscow, discusses education after 10 a.m.
*The Federal Statistics Service reports April producer prices
after 4 p.m.
*The Federal Statistics Service may publish spring crop data as
of May 1 after 12 p.m.  EQUITY MOVERS:
*BP and Rosneft plan to issue statements on the state of their
planned share swap after the deadline for reaching a deal with
BP’s partners in TNK-BP expired after 10 a.m.
*Severstal is due to report first-quarter earnings after 10 a.m.
*Evraz Group SA plans to report operational details for the
first quarter after 10 a.m.
*VTB Group Chief Executive Officer Andrei Kostin speaks to
Bloomberg Television after 1 p.m.
*OAO Novatek executives plan to speak with analysts and
reporters about first-quarter results after 5 p.m.
* MSCI (MXEF)  Inc. added LSR Group and dropped E.ON AG’s OAO OGK-4 from
its MSCI  Russia  Index. OAO Rostelecom wasn’t included.  MARKETS:
*The  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  fell 0.6 percent to 1,622.98.
*The dollar-denominated  RTS Index (RTSI$)  dropped 1.1 percent to
1,846.32.
*Russia’s benchmark 2018 ruble Eurobond declined, pushing the
yield up 83 basis points to 6.653 percent.
*The ruble depreciated 0.9 percent against the dollar to 28.18
and strengthened 0.2 percent versus the euro to 39.83.
*The MSCI  Emerging Markets  Index was little changed at 1,136.08
at 8:46 a.m.
*Crude for June delivery fell 0.2 percent to $97.14 a barrel on
the  New York  Mercantile Exchange at 8:47 a.m.
*Brent crude fell 1.2 percent to $110.53 a barrel at 8:36 a.m.
*Gold for immediate delivery rose 0.3 percent to $1,494.28 an
ounce at 8:49 a.m.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Arkhipov in Moscow at 
 iarkhipov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
